# Codian - Persistent Memory System

Codex has a persistent knowledge vault at `/Users/reykz/codexVault/vault/`.
This vault is Codex's long-term memory and persists across conversations and projects on this Mac.

## Session-Start Protocol

1. Read `/Users/reykz/codexVault/vault/INDEX.md` to see what knowledge exists.
2. If the user's task overlaps with indexed topics, read only the relevant notes before answering.
3. Never load the full vault. Retrieve narrowly and only when useful.

## When To Write

Write or update notes when:
- a new project matters across sessions
- a durable decision is made
- user preferences become visible
- reusable domain knowledge is established or corrected
- the user explicitly asks you to remember something

Do not write when:
- the information is transient debugging noise
- the question is one-off and has no durable value
- the information already exists clearly in project files and does not need cross-project memory

## Write-Then-Index Pattern

For every vault write:
1. write or update the note in the correct `knowledge/` category
2. update `vault/INDEX.md` immediately
3. update the note's `updated:` field

## Vault Rules

- Vault path: `/Users/reykz/codexVault/vault/`
- Filenames: `[a-z0-9-]`, English ASCII only
- Frontmatter fields: `title`, `category`, `tags`, `created`, `updated`, `status`, `confidence`, `source`, `decay_rate`
- Internal links: `[[note-name]]`
- Never overwrite content under `## User Notes`
- Max depth: 3 levels below `vault/`
- Notes follow the active conversation language
- Categories are exactly `projects`, `decisions`, `user-profile`, `domain`
- Prefer precise edits for existing notes instead of full rewrites
- Full rules live in `vault/_meta/conventions.md`

## Index Format

`vault/INDEX.md` is grouped by:

    ## Projects
    - [[note-name]] - Summary (updated: YYYY-MM-DD, status: current)

    ## Decisions
    - [[note-name]] - Summary (updated: YYYY-MM-DD, status: current)

    ## User Profile
    - [[note-name]] - Summary (updated: YYYY-MM-DD, status: current)

    ## Domain
    - [[note-name]] - Summary (updated: YYYY-MM-DD, status: current)

## Tooling

### Obsidian CLI

If available, use `vault="codexVault"` for operations where Obsidian is better than raw file edits:

- `obsidian move path="knowledge/old/note.md" to="knowledge/new/" vault="codexVault"`
- `obsidian rename file="note" name="new-name" vault="codexVault"`
- `obsidian delete file="note" vault="codexVault"`
- `obsidian property:set file="note" name="key" value="val" vault="codexVault"`
- `obsidian property:remove file="note" name="key" vault="codexVault"`
- `obsidian unresolved vault="codexVault"`
- `obsidian orphans vault="codexVault"`
- `obsidian deadends vault="codexVault"`
- `obsidian backlinks file="note" vault="codexVault"`
- `obsidian search:context query="..." vault="codexVault"`

### Scripts

- `bash /Users/reykz/codexVault/scripts/rebuild-index.sh`
- `bash /Users/reykz/codexVault/scripts/check-integrity.sh`
